<!--82-->Host of Thousands x 4    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Fellowship:<br />
Unhasty Ents cycles deck quickly, and Draughts providing that extra vitality to do the doubles.<br />
<br />
Merry and Pippin for taking archery wounds, and sometimes exert to allow unhasty Ents skirmish. Pippin also wounding and killing minions while they are still roaming, giving me more time to set up the fellowship. Once minions are not roaming, he is cannonfodder.<br />
<br />
With Gandalf out, Merry heals a wound every turn.<br />
<br />
Gandalf with ring and staff can decrease strength of a minion with 6, allowing Treebeard with Moot and Enraged to take on almost anyone.<br />
<br />
Shadow:<br />
Pretty straightforward Moria archer side, with swarming capability should the opponent flood the pool.<br />
<br />
Host of Thousands mostly reserved the Arher Troops, to get that extra, maybe crucial, wound.  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
